{"word":"ἀπαίδευτος","slug":"ἀπαίδευτος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀπαίδευτος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:παιδεύω'><el>παιδεύω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>uneducated</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>:— <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>uninstructed in</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>ignorant, boorish, coarse</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <el>ἀπαιδεύτως ἔχειν</el> to be <i>without education</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}